The paper discusses the analysis of traffic and usage patterns of an Internet portal to a large astronomical catalog archive. The analysis involves data mining of web and SQL logs, and includes topics such as interactive instruction, programmatic and batch-local access, ad-hoc SQL, personal database, and batch job access. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Databases (cs.DB), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), Machine Learning (cs.DL), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
